For nosebleeds,
Do NOT be alarmed by it.

It’s mostly NOT a big deal.
Do NOT blow your nose.
Do NOT sneeze too hard.

Pinch the soft parts of your nose tightly.
Breath through your mouth.
Do this for a few minutes.
The nose bleed will stop.

If heavy bleeding, go to hospital.

text: It brought me back to all the things I missed out on cuz I couldn’t articulate this invisible pain. Now I know what it is, I wonder why not one other person clocked it. Since 2012, I’ve used twitter as a trigger diary because it allows me to be creative with it 💁🏾‍♀️
label: SYMPTOM_TALK

text: I’m sitting here with a mad migraine, just reminiscing on some of my most vivid migraines & it brought me back to childhood when I’d be throwing up in the bathroom and no one knew why. It brought me back to a concert I’d spent 3 months rehearsing for but had to leave on the day.
label: SYMPTOM_TALK

text: But the reality is? A migraine can completely wipe me out for a day and in some cases, up to three days. I didn’t catch something, I wasn’t injured, that’s just how my neurology works.
label: SYMPTOM_TALK

text: Migraines are not headaches, if they were I wouldn’t even be talking about them. Migraines are MF debilitating and even when you know all your triggers, stress will always reign supreme. But the most jarring part had always been trying to prove it to those around me.
label: SYMPTOM_TALK

text: I don’t wish anything upon myself but I do wish there were more blatant indicators for ones pain. It’s everyday explanation and ‘raise awareness’ and ‘I don’t know why we’re not taught this in school’ but reality is people are living it as we speak. There’s no time.
label: SYMPTOM_TALK

text: I shall name this migraine: Maybe if I was born at the right time things could have been worse. But they could also have been better. I also love playing cards because it’s the ultimate metaphor for life.
